11. gloria aucta, etc.: these ab- latives absolute have all the force of ablatives of quality. ln fact, the Ro· mans were not so particular about classifying the uses of cases as it is convenient for us to be. -obtinu- ere: cf. tenuere, 42. 2. — collega . . . datur: in these cases (cf. 42. 2 and 43. 1) the patricians suc- ceeded in forcing one of their par- tisans on the elective body, but were obliged to allow one consul to the supporters of the plebeians; hence the word datur.
